10:26.359 --> 10:27.627
no interruptions
from our phones.

10:27.661 --> 10:29.162
It's kind of liberating.

10:29.196 --> 10:31.098
Yeah, I wish I could
Instagram a picture

10:31.131 --> 10:32.532
of my relaxed
face right now.

10:32.565 --> 10:34.301
GOLDIE:
Oh, baby,

10:34.334 --> 10:35.468
what are you wearing?

10:35.502 --> 10:36.704
It's my pilgrim costume

10:36.737 --> 10:38.038
for my school's
Thanksgiving play.

10:38.071 --> 10:39.372
You are so Kelly McGillis

10:39.406 --> 10:40.540
in Witness right now.

10:40.573 --> 10:42.042
Or Helena
Bonham-Carter
in anything.

10:42.075 --> 10:44.311
Don't you think you're taking
this a little too far, sweetie?

10:44.344 --> 10:45.779
No. You said you wanted
to give up technology.

10:45.813 --> 10:48.015
And if you're truly
serious about that,

10:48.048 --> 10:50.017
if you really want to connect
with your child,

10:50.050 --> 10:52.019
then it shouldn't just include
phones and tablets.

10:52.052 --> 10:54.287
It should include all
modern conveniences.

10:54.321 --> 10:57.124
Unless, you aren't able
to take this seriously.

10:57.157 --> 10:57.825
Oh.

10:57.858 --> 10:58.892
Fine.

10:58.926 --> 10:59.960
Let's do this.

10:59.993 --> 11:00.961
Tonight we're
gonna party

11:00.994 --> 11:03.196
like it's 1799.

11:03.230 --> 11:04.031
Okay.

11:04.064 --> 11:06.033
Uh...
Do we all
get bonnets?

11:06.066 --> 11:07.534
I think I cut
my finger off.

11:07.567 --> 11:09.602
(playing light melody)

11:15.042 --> 11:16.744
Sweetie!
Well done!

11:16.777 --> 11:19.412
What a talent!
So good.

11:19.446 --> 11:21.815
Finally, dinner.

11:21.849 --> 11:23.150
Well, I love
this candlelight.

11:23.183 --> 11:24.517
It makes me look like I'm 14.

11:24.551 --> 11:26.019
Well, technically,
the candles are cheating

11:26.053 --> 11:27.387
because we didn't make
them ourselves.

11:27.420 --> 11:28.722
Yeah, but Martha
Stewart did.

11:28.756 --> 11:29.923
No, she really did.

11:29.957 --> 11:31.224
In her Connecticut
farmhouse.

11:31.258 --> 11:32.525
She rendered
the tallow fat

11:32.559 --> 11:34.594
from her beloved but
slower-moving pets,

11:34.627 --> 11:36.663
and then she added
vanilla beans

11:36.696 --> 11:38.198
and then she poured it
all into molds.

11:38.231 --> 11:40.000
And yeah,
so we're good.

11:40.033 --> 11:42.669
Still, without the technological
advances of modern science,

11:42.702 --> 11:44.504
we wouldn't have antibiotics,

11:44.537 --> 11:46.406
refrigerated foods,
public sanitation.

11:46.439 --> 11:48.942
Our life expectancy
would be 38.

11:48.976 --> 11:50.710
Ticktock, fellas.

11:52.645 --> 11:53.781
Well, these tomatoes
look fabulous.

11:53.814 --> 11:55.749
Are these from
the farmers' market?

11:55.783 --> 11:57.851
No, I got them from the
neighbors across the way.

11:57.885 --> 11:59.019
They have a whole garden,

11:59.052 --> 12:00.220
and they're really nice
about sharing.

12:00.253 --> 12:01.388
The neighbors
in the brick house?

12:01.421 --> 12:02.555
People live there?

12:02.589 --> 12:04.624
They can totally see into
your master bathroom

12:04.657 --> 12:06.026
from their guest room balcony.

12:06.059 --> 12:08.261
(chokes)
See? When we put down

12:08.295 --> 12:09.596
our electronic gadgets,

12:09.629 --> 12:10.864
it really gives
us a chance

12:10.898 --> 12:12.065
to connect with people.

12:12.099 --> 12:13.600
Yeah, because before
we had all these gadgets,

12:13.633 --> 12:15.368
it was downright barbaric.

12:15.402 --> 12:17.437
Yeah, Shania, houses
only had one phone

12:17.470 --> 12:18.605
and they were connected
to the wall

12:18.638 --> 12:20.473
with a cord. And then
if you were trying to

12:20.507 --> 12:22.209
reach somebody who was already
talking to somebody else,

12:22.242 --> 12:23.376
you would hear
this terrible sound.

12:23.410 --> 12:25.145
It would go err, err, err!

12:25.178 --> 12:26.914
DAVID:
And when you wanted
the news, an old,

12:26.947 --> 12:28.916
out-of-shape white man
would come on your television

12:28.949 --> 12:31.051
at 6:00 p.m. and actually
read it to you.

12:31.084 --> 12:32.219
Things were simpler

12:32.252 --> 12:33.420
back then.

12:33.453 --> 12:34.721
I mean, it would be nice

12:34.754 --> 12:36.089
for our kid
to experience that.

12:36.123 --> 12:37.490
Even just
for a little.

12:37.524 --> 12:39.827
I know. 'Cause how often
do we get the opportunity

12:39.860 --> 12:41.428
just to really, you
know, sit around

12:41.461 --> 12:42.629
and talk to each other?

12:42.662 --> 12:44.631
Yeah.

12:44.664 --> 12:46.666
(crickets chirping)

12:50.303 --> 12:51.304
I'm gonna use
the restroom.

12:51.338 --> 12:52.305
Awesome.
Yeah.

12:52.339 --> 12:53.673
