* You remember FranÃ§ois

15:46.279 --> 15:47.814
* The time you got
the Lady Dis *

15:47.847 --> 15:50.083
* On the cruise to Panama...

15:50.117 --> 15:51.618
Okay, you guys.

15:51.651 --> 15:52.952
(music stops)

15:52.986 --> 15:55.422
Phones, gadgets,
anything with a screen,

15:55.455 --> 15:56.956
put 'em in here.

15:56.990 --> 15:58.458
Come on, come on.

15:58.491 --> 16:00.927
No more technology
at work, you guys.

16:00.960 --> 16:02.762
It's unprofessional,
it's a time-suck.

16:02.795 --> 16:03.963
Get it in.

16:03.997 --> 16:05.332
In, in, in.
No phones,

16:05.365 --> 16:07.167
no PDAs. If you
have to bring in

16:07.200 --> 16:08.201
a source of
information,

16:08.235 --> 16:09.469
bring in a newspaper.

16:09.502 --> 16:11.004
You, too, Devin.

16:11.038 --> 16:12.205
No, no, no, no.

16:12.239 --> 16:13.406
I don't have time
for your acting.

16:14.474 --> 16:16.309
Quick, quick, quick.

16:16.343 --> 16:17.844
Get it in.
Oh, come on.

16:17.877 --> 16:19.212
Be smarter
than the trash can.

16:19.246 --> 16:21.214
So now that we're free

16:21.248 --> 16:23.050
of all of this
nonsense,

16:23.083 --> 16:25.018
we can focus
on our craft.

16:25.052 --> 16:26.119
Now, we have
a big Carly Rae Jep...

16:26.153 --> 16:27.387
Mmm.

16:27.420 --> 16:28.821
What's happening?
Mmm.

16:29.856 --> 16:31.591
Mmm.
Okay.

16:32.659 --> 16:33.793
We saw your video,

16:33.826 --> 16:35.162
and the side you
show America

16:35.195 --> 16:36.696
is so raw and
authentic. It's like

16:36.729 --> 16:38.365
you pulled back the curtains
to show everybody

16:38.398 --> 16:42.369
who you really are.
I mean, that is so brave, man.

16:42.402 --> 16:44.204
Mm-hmm.
Hmm.

16:44.237 --> 16:45.638
You can un-pucker.
You still can't

16:45.672 --> 16:46.806
have time off
to sing at the Nobel

16:46.839 --> 16:48.675
Peace Prize ceremony.

16:48.708 --> 16:50.743
Clea.
I'm so glad the
Twitter-sphere sees you

16:50.777 --> 16:52.212
the way I see
my Bry-Bry,

16:52.245 --> 16:53.846
a kindhearted
open soul,

16:53.880 --> 16:55.415
not afraid
to sing his feelings.

16:55.448 --> 16:57.217
You can keep your phone.
You're my favorite.

16:57.250 --> 16:58.751
I heart you.
I heart you.

16:58.785 --> 16:59.719
"Thank you

16:59.752 --> 17:01.354
@NanaUrBusiness and

17:01.388 --> 17:03.890
@MrBryanCollins for showing
us all what real love is."

17:03.923 --> 17:05.858
(gasps)
#Bryan-Is-A-Softie

17:05.892 --> 17:07.060
is trending.
Huh, wha-what?

17:07.094 --> 17:07.794
Whoo!

17:10.363 --> 17:12.065
Okay, okay, you guys.

17:12.099 --> 17:14.601
Now, the next ten minutes
of this dance rehearsal,

17:14.634 --> 17:17.870
I want you all to retweet
my video to your followers.

17:17.904 --> 17:19.372
Come on. Retweet!

17:19.406 --> 17:20.407
Retweet party!

17:20.440 --> 17:22.242
Come on!
Quick, quick, quick.

17:22.275 --> 17:23.376
Tweet, tweet, tweet.

17:23.410 --> 17:25.712
This is the power
of social media, you guys.

17:25.745 --> 17:27.647
Use it for good!

17:30.217 --> 17:31.751
Mother.

17:31.784 --> 17:32.919
Mother,

17:32.952 --> 17:34.387
dawn is breaking.

17:34.421 --> 17:35.855
Mother.

17:35.888 --> 17:36.889
Mom!

17:36.923 --> 17:38.858
What? What is it?
Are you okay?

17:38.891 --> 17:40.293
The sun is near risen.

17:40.327 --> 17:42.095
There's hardly time
to start the fire

17:42.129 --> 17:43.596
to boil water for our baths.

17:43.630 --> 17:45.565
It's pitch-black out.
No matter.

17:45.598 --> 17:47.234
We must grind the corn
for bread,

17:47.267 --> 17:48.901
there are socks
that need darning...

17:48.935 --> 17:50.103
Okay, okay.

17:50.137 --> 17:51.003
I get it.

17:52.805 --> 17:53.940
You win.

17:55.575 --> 17:56.309
(groans)

17:56.343 --> 17:57.444
Here.

17:57.477 --> 17:59.078
Just please

17:59.112 --> 18:01.314
let me sleep.
And promise me

18:01.348 --> 18:02.949
if we're ever in front
of your friends' parents

18:02.982 --> 18:04.617
and I say
I only let you have

18:04.651 --> 18:06.153
one hour
of screen time a day,

18:06.186 --> 18:07.787
you won't call me out
as a liar.

18:08.955 --> 18:11.324
Thank God I'm part
of the world again.

18:11.358 --> 18:14.327
But, Mom, I did learn
something from all this.

18:14.361 --> 18:16.896
I'll use these
devices responsibly,

18:16.929 --> 18:19.399
as the powerful
tools they are,

18:19.432 --> 18:22.569
an evolutionary step
in human connection.

18:22.602 --> 18:25.305
But I also value
hands-on experiences.

18:25.338 --> 18:28.241
I mean, you can watch a
video on how to bake bread,

18:28.275 --> 18:30.677
but you can't feel the dough
between your fingers

18:30.710 --> 18:32.245
or smell it baking

18:32.279 --> 18:35.014
or share the laughter
and closeness that we...

18:35.047 --> 18:36.616
Mom?

18:54.634 --> 18:55.968
Well, I am proud of us.

18:56.002 --> 18:58.037
Two nights in a row,

18:58.070 --> 19:00.173
living tech-free,
going off the grid.

19:00.207 --> 19:02.175
I feel like a
frontier man.

19:02.209 --> 19:04.177
A frontier man
who wears eye cream.

19:04.211 --> 19:05.278
(chuckles)

19:05.312 --> 19:07.547
It was nice having
a candlelit dinner with you

19:07.580 --> 19:09.182
and talking about
potential baby names.

19:09.216 --> 19:10.450
I love that. I mean,

19:10.483 --> 19:12.018
when was the last time
we spent a Saturday night

19:12.051 --> 19:13.386
not checking our e-mails

19:13.420 --> 19:15.021
and watching
48 Hours Mystery?

19:15.054 --> 19:16.055
I don't know,
I kind of missed seeing

19:16.088 --> 19:17.390
what the title
was tonight though.

19:17.424 --> 19:18.291
That's true.

19:18.325 --> 19:19.559
"Nightmare in Napa."

19:19.592 --> 19:20.793
(laughs)

19:20.827 --> 19:23.029
"Two Wigs, a Gun,
and a Murder."

19:23.062 --> 19:24.897
"The Lady in the Pool."

19:24.931 --> 19:26.899
(laughing)

19:26.933 --> 19:28.801
You know, we haven't
talked about it yet,

19:28.835 --> 19:30.537
but that video
that you made...

19:30.570 --> 19:32.505
Oh, David...

19:33.540 --> 19:35.708
I'm sorry it went so public.

19:35.742 --> 19:36.409
I loved it.

19:36.443 --> 19:38.044
You did?
Yeah.

19:38.077 --> 19:39.746
I mean, I know that
a billion people saw it but...

19:39.779 --> 19:42.349
all this talk about us
not connecting,

19:42.382 --> 19:44.751
that song reminded me
of how much we share.

19:46.386 --> 19:49.856
I loved our jaunts
to San Francisco

19:49.889 --> 19:52.158
and holding hands
in the fog,

19:52.191 --> 19:53.760
muddling mojitos.

19:53.793 --> 19:56.729
